---
import Layout from '~/layouts/InquiryLayout.astro';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
---

<Layout metadata={{ title: 'RFQ Guide — How to Get an Accurate Quote | EVAPFit', ignoreTitleTemplate: true }}>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-slate-950 text-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-14 lg:py-18 text-center">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-400">Quote Guide</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk Variable', sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.03em;">
        How to Get an Accurate Quote
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-400 leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto">
        The more detail you provide, the faster and more accurate your quote will be. Here's exactly what we need.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Checklist -->
  <section class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-900">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-12 lg:py-16">
      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">1</span>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Product Identification</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-11 space-y-3 text-sm text-muted">
          <p>Tell us exactly which product(s) you're interested in. If you found it on our site, include the product name. If not, describe what it does and which system it belongs to (water, electrical, evaporation, etc.).</p>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-800/50">
            <p class="text-xs font-medium text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">Good example:</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted italic">"Replacement Water Pump 110V — your catalog page shows this as model WP-110V-15W. We need the threaded 1/2" inlet version."</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">2</span>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Quantity & Budget</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-11 space-y-3 text-sm text-muted">
          <p>Estimated quantity per SKU. If you're unsure about final volume, give a range (e.g., 500-1000 pcs). Also mention if you want sample pricing first, or if you have a target price range.</p>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-800/50">
            <p class="text-xs font-medium text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">Good example:</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted italic">"Initial order 500 pcs, with potential for 2000 pcs/quarter ongoing. Target price under $15/pc FOB. Would like to test 2 sample units first."</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">3</span>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Interface & Dimensions</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-11 space-y-3 text-sm text-muted">
          <p>This is the most critical section. The interface type determines whether the part will physically fit your cooler. Provide as much detail as possible:</p>
          <div class="grid gap-2 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-3 dark:border-slate-700"><span class="text-xs font-medium text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">For Pumps</span><p class="text-xs text-muted mt-0.5">Inlet/outlet thread size, overall dimensions, mounting hole spacing</p></div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-3 dark:border-slate-700"><span class="text-xs font-medium text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">For Motors</span><p class="text-xs text-muted mt-0.5">Shaft diameter (mm), mounting type (B3/B5/B14), frame size</p></div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-3 dark:border-slate-700"><span class="text-xs font-medium text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">For Cooling Pads</span><p class="text-xs text-muted mt-0.5">Width × height × thickness (mm), flute angle, material type</p></div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-3 dark:border-slate-700"><span class="text-xs font-medium text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">For Valves/Filters</span><p class="text-xs text-muted mt-0.5">Port size, connection type (thread/push-fit), body dimensions</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">4</span>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Electrical Specifications</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-11 space-y-3 text-sm text-muted">
          <p>If your part is electrical, include these parameters. Mismatched electrical specs can damage equipment or create safety hazards.</p>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-4 dark:border-amber-800 dark:bg-amber-900/10">
            <p class="text-xs text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300"><strong>Critical:</strong> Voltage must match exactly. A 220V motor connected to 110V won't run; a 110V motor on 220V will burn out.</p>
          </div>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>&bull; Voltage (V) and Frequency (Hz) — e.g., 220V/50Hz</li>
            <li>&bull; Power (W) or Current (A) — e.g., 550W</li>
            <li>&bull; RPM — e.g., 1400 RPM</li>
            <li>&bull; Capacitor value if applicable — e.g., 6µF</li>
            <li>&bull; IP rating if outdoor use — e.g., IP44</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 5 -->
      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">5</span>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Photos</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-11 space-y-3 text-sm text-muted">
          <p>Photos are the single fastest way to get an accurate match. Include:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>&bull; Front view — the whole part, clearly visible</li>
            <li>&bull; Close-up of the connection point — thread, flange, or fitting</li>
            <li>&bull; Any labels, part numbers, or markings on the part</li>
            <li>&bull; A ruler or coin next to the part for scale reference</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 6 -->
      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">6</span>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Shipping & Delivery</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-11 space-y-3 text-sm text-muted">
          <p>Help us quote the best shipping option:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1">
            <li>&bull; Destination country and port/airport</li>
            <li>&bull; Preferred Incoterms — FOB, CIF, DDP, or EXW</li>
            <li>&bull; Any special packaging or labeling requirements</li>
            <li>&bull; Target delivery date if you have a deadline</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What Happens Next -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-teal-200 bg-teal-50/50 p-6 dark:border-teal-800 dark:bg-teal-900/10">
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-teal-800 dark:text-teal-300 flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="tabler:clock" class="h-5 w-5"/> What Happens After You Submit
        </h3>
        <div class="mt-4 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-3 text-sm">
          <div><span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Within 24 Hours</span><p class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">Confirmation and any clarification questions.</p></div>
          <div><span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">1-2 Business Days</span><p class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">Detailed quote with pricing, MOQ, and lead time.</p></div>
          <div><span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">After Approval</span><p class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">Sample production begins. Bulk order after sample approval.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-slate-950 text-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-14 text-center lg:py-18">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk Variable', sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">Ready to Request a Quote?</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base text-gray-400 max-w-xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">Your inquiry list items will be pre-filled in the form. Include the details above for the fastest, most accurate response.</p>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <a href="/inquiry" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-teal-600 px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition-colors hover:bg-teal-500">
          <Icon name="tabler:mail" class="h-4 w-4"/> Submit Inquiry
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
